    <p>Thinking yourself into your opponentâ€™s position seldom works. The requisite mental leap is too great, the motivation lacking. In order to genuinely understand someone, you have to adopt their positionâ€”not intellectually but in actual fact. You have to step into their shoes and experience your opponentâ€™s situation first-hand</p>
