    <p>Itâ€™s worth slipping into other peopleâ€™s shoes and actually walking around in them. Do it with the most important relationships in your lifeâ€”your partner, your clients, your employees, your voters (if youâ€™re a politician). Role reversal is by far the most efficient, quick and cost-effective way of building mutual understanding. Be the proverbial king who dressed as a beggar to mingle among his subjects. And because thatâ€™s not always possible, hereâ€™s another recommendation: read novels. Being immersed in a good novel, accompanying the protagonist throughout both highs and lows, is an efficient workaround that sits somewhere between thinking and doing</p>
